Effect.definition: something that is produced by an agent or cause 2 pl
Effect.origin: [the right of the people to be secure in their persons, houses, papers, and s , against unreasonable searches and seizures " U.S. Constitution amend. IV"]

1.definition: to cause to come into being

2.definition: to bring about often by surmounting obstacles [ a settlement of the dispute]

3.definition: to put into operation [the duty of the legislature to the will of the citizens]
